The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Bangla fillip for exporters
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Bangla fillip for exporters
          A STAFF REPORTER                      T.C.A Ranganathan in Calcutta on Thursday. A Telegraph picture                          
	Calcutta, July 15: The Exim Bank of India plans to offer $1 billion of credit to exporters participating in Bangladeshs infrastructure development, chairman and managing director T.C.A. Ranganathan said here today.        
	Besides, the bank will provide $700-800 million for exports primarily to Sri Lanka plus an additional cash prop for Africa.         
	Prime Minister Manmohan Singh had announced a financial assistance of $1 billion to the Sheikh Hasina government. We are participating in this programme, he said on the sidelines of a seminar organised by the Confederation of Indian Industry.         
	The credit will be used to build railway bridges, supply locomotives and dredging eqipment.        
	Ranganathan said the bank was also focusing on strengthening the cluster approach for exporters and helping small and medium enterprises to achieve scale.                                                                                                                                       
